Aljos wins have been dominant but they’ve been against corpses of the guys we used to know. Kattar hasn’t been the same since the Allen fight and Ortega has been one of the most washed/overrated fighters for some time. Beating him for the majority of the fight isn’t that impressive because almost the entirety of his wins are comebacks. He also died making weight and shouldn’t have even competed that night, yet Aljo ran on the backfoot the entire time and gassed out hard in the champ rounds against a guy who was there for a paycheck

